      • isUserVisible

        boolean isUserVisible()
        Tells whether related object is made visible in the GUI.

        The current value depends on the currently logged user rights on the object.

        Returns:
        true if the element is visible in GUI, else false.

        boolean isVisible()
        Tells whether the related element is made visible in the GUI.

        This metho

        Returns:
        true if the element is visible in the explorer and other views, else false.

      • isBrowse

        boolean isBrowse()
        Tells whether related object is browsable (visiting its dependencies).

        The current value is the intersection of the currently logged user rights on the object, the current state of the application (licences) and the intrinsic rights set on the object.

        Returns:
        true if the element is visible in GUI, else false.

      • isWrite

        boolean isWrite()
        Tells whether related object is writable.

        The current value is the intersection of the currently logged user rights on the object, the current state of the application (licences) and the intrinsic rights set on the object.

        Note: an object that is writable is not necessarly modifiable.

        Returns:
        true if the element is visible in GUI, else false.
        See Also:
        isModifiable()

      • isCmsSync

        boolean isCmsSync()
        When a CMS is used (or a similar tool), tells whether the related object needs an update from its CMS repository.
        Returns:
        true if the object needs an update, else false.

      • isCmsModified

        boolean isCmsModified()
        When a CMS is used (or a similar tool), tells whether the related object has been locally modified (by reference to its CMS repository).
        Returns:
        true if the object has been locally modified, else false.

      • isCmsToAdd

        boolean isCmsToAdd()
        When a CMS is used (or a similar tool), tells whether the related object is planned for adding to the CMS repository (most often at next commit).
        Returns:
        true if the object is planned for adding, else false.

      • isCmsToDelete

        boolean isCmsToDelete()
        When a CMS is used (or a similar tool), tells whether the related object is planned for removing from the CMS repository (most often at next commit).
        Returns:
        true if the object is planned for removing, else false.

      • isCmsReadOnly

        boolean isCmsReadOnly()
        When a CMS is used (or a similar tool), tells whether the related object is read only at the CMS level.
        Returns:
        true if the object is read only at the CMS level, else false.

      • isCmsManaged

        boolean isCmsManaged()
        Tells whether the related object is under CMS management.
        Returns:
        true if the object is under CMS management, else false.

      • isCmsConflict

        boolean isCmsConflict()
        Tells whether the related object is in CMS conflict.
        Returns:
        true if the object is in CMS conflict, else false.

      • isRamc

        boolean isRamc()
        Tells whether the related object belongs to a Model Component (RAMC), meaning that its definition is partial.
        Returns:
        true if the object is part of a model component, else false.

      • isShell

        boolean isShell()
        Tells whether the related object is a shell object.

        Shell objects are objects that are not currently reachable for some reasons, and detailed contents is not available.

        Returns:
        true if the object is a shell object, else false.

      • isDeleted

        boolean isDeleted()
        Tells whether the related object is deleted.
        Returns:
        true if the object is deleted, else false.

      • isModifiable

        boolean isModifiable()
        Tells whether related object is modifiable.

        An object is modifiable if all the following conditions are met:

        • it is writable.
        • it is not a model component.
        • it is not locked by the CMS.
        • it is not a shell object.
        • it is not deleted.
        Returns:
        true if the element is visible in GUI, else false.

      • isLockingNeeded

        boolean isLockingNeeded()
        Tells whether a lock must be taken before modifying the related object.

        This usually depends on the versioned fragment the related object belongs to.

        Returns:
        true if locking is needed, else false.

      • isDirty

        boolean isDirty()
        Tells whether has been modified since last model save.

        May answer true for a whole set of object (eg: a CMS node) if only one of them is modified.

        Returns:
        true if the object needs to be saved.
